Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.15,0:00:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to this month’s broadcast.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.92,0:00:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Here are a few highlights
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.92,0:00:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,of what we’ll enjoy on the program.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.76,0:00:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What if changing circumstances in the family
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.83,0:00:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,begin pushing mates apart emotionally?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.76,0:00:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,This dramatization of Shaan and Kiara
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.80,0:00:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,may provide some timely guidance.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.20,0:00:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, the story of Grace Li
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.64,0:00:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,will be an encouragement to any who have faced
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.11,0:00:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,severe emotional challenges\Nfor taking a stand for the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.18,0:00:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll see the effect\Nthat her actions had on those around her.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.88,0:00:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And this month’s music video
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.89,0:00:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,will reassure us of the love, kindness,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.72,0:00:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and support we enjoy as Jehovah’s people.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.09,0:00:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,All that and more on this February 2019 edition
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.10,0:00:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of JW Broadcasting!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.25,0:01:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The theme of this program
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.59,0:01:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is taken from the second part
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.56,0:01:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of Romans 12:10:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.59,0:01:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“In showing honor to one another,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.69,0:01:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,take the lead.”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.83,0:01:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What is honor?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.83,0:01:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Hebrew Scriptures,\Nthe term translated “honor”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.07,0:01:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,literally means “heaviness.”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.84,0:01:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we honor someone,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.97,0:01:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re acknowledging that he’s weighty
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.08,0:01:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,or that he amounts to something.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.48,0:01:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Greek Scriptures,\Nthe word is related
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.95,0:01:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to setting a price on something,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.28,0:01:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,meaning that the one we honor\Nis esteemed or has value.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.29,0:01:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Whom should we honor?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.56,0:01:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, Jehovah is worthy of honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.16,0:01:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Revelation 4:11 says this
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.33,0:01:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and gives us the reason\Nfor giving glory and honor to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.80,0:02:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It says because he “created all things.”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.14,0:02:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He is responsible\Nfor us having life in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.85,0:02:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we give him honor?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.88,0:02:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There are many ways:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.88,0:02:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We honor him by doing his will
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.22,0:02:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,—obeying his laws and principles.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.75,0:02:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We honor him\Nby extolling his qualities and promises
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.76,0:02:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,—telling others\Nabout these gifts from God.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.13,0:02:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We show him honor\Nby contributing financially
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.36,0:02:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to the worldwide educational work
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.63,0:02:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that he’s directing\Nthrough his Son and holy spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.11,0:02:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And just as Revelation chapter 4 said
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.08,0:02:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,about Jehovah being worthy of the honor,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.35,0:02:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Revelation 5:12
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.42,0:02:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,says that his Son, Christ Jesus,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.82,0:02:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,is worthy of the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.99,0:02:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 12 says of Jesus:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.19,0:02:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“They were saying with a loud voice:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.43,0:02:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘The Lamb who was slaughtered
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.43,0:03:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘is worthy to receive\Nthe power and riches and wisdom
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.26,0:03:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and strength and honor\Nand glory and blessing.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.04,0:03:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we show honor to Jesus?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.04,0:03:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,One way is acknowledged\Nin the verse we just read.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.61,0:03:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He was “slaughtered”\Nlike a sacrificial lamb
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.18,0:03:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we might have the hope\Nof everlasting life.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.88,0:03:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We highly esteem,\Nand value, that sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.42,0:03:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We honor Jesus\Nby recognizing his role
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.46,0:03:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,as an immortal\N“King of kings” in the heavens.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.49,0:03:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And another\Nvery practical way to honor Jesus
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.00,0:03:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is to strive to imitate\Nhis life and personality
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.47,0:03:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,as the model for us to follow closely.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.97,0:03:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If we take the lead in showing honor,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.67,0:03:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,who else will we view\Nas highly valued
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.11,0:03:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,—to be treated with esteem?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.28,0:03:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Ephesians 6:1, 2 says
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.48,0:03:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that children ‘honor their father and mother’\Nwhen they’re obedient to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.42,0:03:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Matthew 15:4-6
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.25,0:03:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,makes it clear that adult children
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.89,0:04:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,honor their parents and grandparents
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.89,0:04:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,by giving material assistance\Nto them as needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.76,0:04:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,First Timothy 5:17
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.13,0:04:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,urges us to give elders “double honor”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.17,0:04:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,because of their hard work in our behalf.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.97,0:04:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Romans 13:1, 7
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.77,0:04:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,even extends\Nthe matter of showing honor
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.91,0:04:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to governmental rulers\Nand others in authority.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.78,0:04:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,First Peter 2:17
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.52,0:04:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,broadens the meaning\Nof honor even further saying:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.95,0:04:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“Honor men of all sorts.”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.79,0:04:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition to being kind\Nand respectful to people in general,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.29,0:04:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,we also honor them\Nby being willing
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.56,0:04:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to spend time\Nsharing the good news with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.23,0:04:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Ephesians 5:22-25
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.74,0:04:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,appeals to wives\Nto honor their husbands
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.71,0:04:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,by having Christlike subjection for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.94,0:04:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Husbands are to honor their wives\Nby showing them love
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.08,0:05:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and treating them\Njust as Jesus treated the congregation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.62,0:05:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And what about our theme text\Nfor this discussion?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.49,0:05:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Who was Paul addressing\Nin Romans chapter 12 when he said:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.86,0:05:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“In showing honor to one another,\Ntake the lead”?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.80,0:05:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are\Nthe “one another” in that verse?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.34,0:05:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at Romans 1:7 with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.67,0:05:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul says he’s writing\N“to all those who are in Rome
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.01,0:05:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,as God’s beloved ones,\Ncalled to be holy ones.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.02,0:05:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So all of us\Nin the Christian congregation
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.99,0:05:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,are to have honor for each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.72,0:05:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d like to spend\Nthe balance of my time
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.49,0:05:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,discussing two\Nof the many opportunities
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.56,0:05:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we have to show honor
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.00,0:05:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,(they’re the last two\Nthat I just referenced):
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.23,0:05:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,first, marriage mates\Nshowing honor to each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.64,0:05:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and second, showing honor\Nto one another in our congregations.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.01,0:06:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Marriages in general today\Nare seriously lacking in honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.95,0:06:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Marriage mates\Noften demean one another
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.82,0:06:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,with harsh words\Nand disrespectful attitudes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.06,0:06:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Some in the world resort\Nto physical violence,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.03,0:06:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,as if that somehow\Nmakes the abusive one right
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.03,0:06:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,in his view of whatever the issue is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.63,0:06:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And infidelity on the part\Nof one or both mates is so common
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.20,0:06:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn’t even\Nraise eyebrows anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.77,0:06:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All of this is a gross\Nlack of honor in marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.81,0:06:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But what about marriages
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.81,0:06:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,of those professing\Nto be Jehovah’s Witnesses?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.45,0:06:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re blessed\Nwith so many marriages
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.49,0:06:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that are wholesome and honorable.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.52,0:06:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,True, none are perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.06,0:06:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But how blessed we are\Nto have the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.86,0:06:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and to have learned to be\Nmore and more Christlike with each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.13,0:07:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve learned to shed things\Nthat we heard when we were growing up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.00,0:07:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the matter\Nof honoring our marriage mate
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.98,0:07:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,needs to be discussed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.14,0:07:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,While relatively few of our marriages
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.95,0:07:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,end up with some kind\Nof physical violence
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.22,0:07:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and relatively few\Nend up in divorce,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.69,0:07:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,what about having honor\Nin the marriage?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.36,0:07:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,After living together\Nas husband and wife
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.86,0:07:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,for many months\Nor for years or even for decades,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.43,0:07:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,familiarity can cause us
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.57,0:07:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to treat each other\Nwith less respect or honor
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.87,0:07:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,than when we were courting.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.04,0:07:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That isn’t right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.14,0:07:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn’t Christlike.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.64,0:07:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But with our inherited imperfection,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.48,0:07:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,we may succumb\Nto dishonorable words and behavior
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.55,0:07:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,with the one\Nthat we promised to treasure
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.89,0:07:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,“until death do us part.”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.29,0:07:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we get a grip\Non this trait and minimize the times
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.33,0:08:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that we have\Na clash of spirit and words?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.76,0:08:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,First, let’s consider
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.53,0:08:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the two basic responsibilities\Nassigned to marriage mates.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.64,0:08:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the foundation
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.64,0:08:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that we can then build on to improve.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.18,0:08:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The role of the husband\Nis clearly stated
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.35,0:08:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,at 1 Corinthians 11:3.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.82,0:08:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And while some wives in society\Nmay bristle at this thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.42,0:08:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,wives serving Jehovah\Nare to embrace this thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.56,0:08:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s the arrangement of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.00,0:08:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,First Corinthians 11:3 says:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.57,0:08:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“But I want you to know\Nthat the head of every man is the Christ;
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.57,0:08:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“in turn, the head\Nof a woman is the man;
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.21,0:08:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,in turn, the head of the Christ is God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.94,0:08:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,God’s Word says\Nthat “the head of a woman is the man.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.68,0:08:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the head of the woman
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.52,0:08:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is not to be a domineering man,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.09,0:09:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,not an abusive man\N—verbally or physically.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.12,0:09:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He is to imitate his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.36,0:09:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And who is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.36,0:09:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What did the first part\Nof the verse say?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.70,0:09:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,“The head\Nof every man is the Christ.”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.10,0:09:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, Ephesians chapter 5
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.47,0:09:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,strikes this fine balance\Nbetween being a head of the wife
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.51,0:09:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and being\Na loving head like the Christ.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.41,0:09:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Ephesians 5:22, 23 says:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.42,0:09:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“Let wives be in subjection\Nto their husbands as to the Lord,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.22,0:09:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,“[But what of the disposition\Nof the husband?]
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.39,0:09:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“because a husband\Nis head of his wife
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.16,0:09:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“just as the Christ\Nis head of the congregation,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.73,0:09:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,he being a savior of this body.”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.47,0:09:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That verse says it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.80,0:09:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 33 of the same chapter says this:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.58,0:09:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“Each one of you\Nmust love his wife as he does himself;
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.25,0:09:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“on the other hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.25,0:10:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the wife should have\Ndeep respect for her husband.”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.55,0:10:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s nowhere in God’s Word
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.16,0:10:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that says that if one mate\Npushes the other mate’s button
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.16,0:10:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,—emotionally—\Nthat it cancels
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.73,0:10:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the offended mate’s obligation\Nto be Christlike.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.57,0:10:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem is that\Nwhen one mate is offended or hurt,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.80,0:10:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s so easy to roll the eyes in disgust
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.28,0:10:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,or to lash back with a verbal insult.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.85,0:10:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the other mate fires back\Nwith another harsh, cutting remark.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.22,0:10:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s like wind on a forest fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.45,0:10:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Tempers blaze,\Nand the evening goes up in smoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.86,0:10:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not at all Christlike.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.66,0:10:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no honor shown\Nin such a conflagration.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.40,0:10:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to stop sooner rather than later.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.74,0:11:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The January 15, 2015,\Nissue of The Watchtower said this:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.64,0:11:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“Remember that marriage\Nis not a competition
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.31,0:11:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“to find out who is stronger,\Nwho can shout louder,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.72,0:11:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“or who can think\Nof the most cutting remark.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.85,0:11:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,“True, we all have flaws,\Nand sometimes we upset others.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.29,0:11:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“But there is never a justifiable reason
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.86,0:11:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“for either a husband or a wife
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.26,0:11:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,“to use sarcastic and demeaning speech,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.13,0:11:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,or worse, to shove or hit each other.”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.41,0:11:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we change the atmosphere?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.61,0:11:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone needs to put out the fire
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.28,0:11:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,with the water of God’s Word.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.08,0:11:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Romans 12:10b, again:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.19,0:11:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“In showing honor\Nto one another, take the lead.”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.09,0:11:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the mates must take the lead
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.99,0:11:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,even if at the time\Nthey’re apologizing for their own behavior
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.56,0:12:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,by acknowledging that they\Ndidn’t respond in a Christlike way saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.07,0:12:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“Forgive me.”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.44,0:12:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That same issue\Nof The Watchtower cited two scriptures:
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.48,0:12:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,one for the husband\Nand one for the wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.85,0:12:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll first read Proverbs 17:27.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.65,0:12:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Husbands, listen to this
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.29,0:12:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and apply it prior to a rift
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.02,0:12:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,or even during the conflict.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.79,0:12:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Proverbs 17:27:
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.40,0:12:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,“A man of knowledge\Nrestrains his words,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.03,0:12:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and a discerning man will remain calm.”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.67,0:12:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Husbands, does that describe us?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.31,0:12:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Now wives,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.31,0:12:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,please locate Proverbs 31:26.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.55,0:12:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Does this describe your speech\Neven when some altercation occurs?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.02,0:12:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Proverbs 31:26:
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.43,0:12:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“She opens her mouth in wisdom;
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.96,0:13:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the law of kindness is on her tongue.”
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.90,0:13:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually after a misunderstanding\Nand rash words have been said,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.44,0:13:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,we feel miserable and upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.41,0:13:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We often chastise ourselves\Nfor adding fuel to the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.15,0:13:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,How much better\Nto train ourselves to restrain our words
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.18,0:13:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and remain calm and to speak
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.79,0:13:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,in wisdom and with kindness of tongue.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.66,0:13:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Meet Emil and Firuca Gârbovan\Nfrom Romania.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.06,0:13:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re good examples\Nof how the power of God’s Word
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.36,0:13:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,can mold and change\Nthe attitudes of marriage mates
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.50,0:13:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,who are willing to be guided by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.84,0:13:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It was in 1983 when I met Firuca.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.58,0:13:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I already had two little girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.25,0:13:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,One was seven years old,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.25,0:13:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and the other one was three.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.25,0:13:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I accepted to study the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.49,0:14:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,My husband worked
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.26,0:14:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,as a warrant officer for the police,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.39,0:14:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,so at the beginning,\NI studied in secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.30,0:14:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I decided to tell him the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.00,0:14:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,When I found out
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.30,0:14:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that my wife was studying the Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.94,0:14:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to become
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.07,0:14:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,one of Jehovah’s Witnesses,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.07,0:14:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I became very sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.21,0:14:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And I realized that our marriage
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.81,0:14:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and our family was in danger
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.21,0:14:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,because I only knew bad things
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.45,0:14:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,about Jehovah’s Witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.15,0:14:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He threatened\Nhe would divorce me, and he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.96,0:14:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The divorce was\Na very difficult time in my life
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.16,0:14:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,because I was seven months pregnant\Nwith our third daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.80,0:14:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Following the divorce, my husband\Nwas given the house and custody
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.71,0:14:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,of our two daughters.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.04,0:14:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to leave the house,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.68,0:15:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and I stayed for almost a year\Nwith two families of our brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.32,0:15:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw Jehovah’s love toward me,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.36,0:15:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and I loved Jehovah very much,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.26,0:15:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,but I loved my husband too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.93,0:15:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,One day, as I was walking
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.60,0:15:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and holding the little girl’s hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.10,0:15:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw Firuca’s husband walking toward me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.77,0:15:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,My heart stopped,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.98,0:15:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and I said to myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.48,0:15:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,‘He is going to hit me!’
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.08,0:15:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But Emil was a gentleman.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.68,0:15:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And he took the little girl in his arms,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.89,0:15:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,talked to her for a few minutes,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.52,0:15:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and then he put her back down and left.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.63,0:15:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,When I saw him leaving, I thanked Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.70,0:15:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,because he didn’t beat me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.33,0:15:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1990, I looked for my wife
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.00,0:15:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and I told her\Nthat I would like to remarry her
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.17,0:16:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to reunite our family.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.31,0:16:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And, after a while, she agreed
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.71,0:16:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and step-by-step I started to study.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.98,0:16:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,In 2003, I became
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.72,0:16:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,one of Jehovah’s Witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.16,0:16:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I am very happy that I made this change,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.33,0:16:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and I regret that I didn’t do it sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.26,0:16:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I personally saw
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.60,0:16:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,how the truth can change a person’s life,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.20,0:16:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,even in my own family.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.37,0:16:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Currently, I serve as an elder.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.98,0:16:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And in 2010, I became a regular pioneer.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.88,0:16:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,When I see Emil conduct
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.72,0:16:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the Bible study next to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.79,0:16:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like kneeling rather than standing
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.59,0:16:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to thank Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.03,0:16:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So to married couples\Nwho love Jehovah we repeat:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.43,0:17:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“In showing honor . . . , take the lead.”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.00,0:17:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The principles just discussed\Ncan also be applied
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.14,0:17:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,when showing honor\Nto others in the congregation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.48,0:17:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Like the husband and wife\Nthat we just discussed,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.55,0:17:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,all of us should be improving\Nin imitating Jesus
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.55,0:17:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and in ‘following his steps closely’\Nin all of our interactions
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.12,0:17:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,with fellow believers\Nin the congregation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.02,0:17:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we show honor\Nto one another?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.53,0:17:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,One way is well described
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.59,0:17:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,at 1 Corinthians 10:23, 24.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.10,0:17:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We show honor\Nwhen we put the other person’s feelings
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.90,0:17:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and needs ahead of our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.57,0:17:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,First Corinthians 10:23, 24:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.24,0:17:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,“All things are lawful,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.01,0:17:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“but not all things are advantageous.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.55,0:17:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,“All things are lawful,\Nbut not all things build up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.15,0:17:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,“Let each one keep seeking,\Nnot his own advantage,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.49,0:17:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,but that of the other person.”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.66,0:18:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We show honor\Nwhen we suppress our own rights.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.66,0:18:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What we do or say might be lawful,\Nbut is it advantageous?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.57,0:18:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Will it build up?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.97,0:18:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 24, then, concisely says it:
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.07,0:18:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“Keep seeking,\Nnot [our] own advantage [or right],
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.94,0:18:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,but that of the other person.”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.55,0:18:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We show honor to others\Nwhen we do good deeds for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.35,0:18:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Possibly, it’s even a humble task
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.45,0:18:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that an elderly publisher needs done.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.09,0:18:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It could be offering to clean the house,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.29,0:18:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,take them to the store,\Nor fill some other need.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.33,0:18:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The principle is at Luke 22:26:
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.67,0:18:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“You, though,\Nare not to be that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.47,0:18:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“But let the one\Nwho is the greatest among you
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.97,0:18:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“become as the youngest,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.97,0:18:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and the one taking the lead\Nas the one ministering.”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.38,0:18:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Earlier, I cited 1 Timothy 5:17,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.25,0:18:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,where we’re urged\Nto give elders “double honor”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.29,0:18:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,because of their hard work in our behalf.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.92,0:19:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re also part\Nof our congregation and deserve honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.69,0:19:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,In our August program last year,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.89,0:19:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Lett helped us consider\Nmuch of what is involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.50,0:19:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll recall that his subject was
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.33,0:19:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“Appreciating Our ‘Gifts in Men.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.90,0:19:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We minister to or honor others
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.61,0:19:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,when we readily forgive them
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.61,0:19:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,if they’ve embarrassed us\Nor hurt our feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.58,0:19:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Overall, Jehovah’s people do quite well
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.82,0:19:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,in honoring one another \Nin the congregation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.55,0:19:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But here is the question:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.69,0:19:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we improving in this aspect
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.96,0:19:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,of our Christian personality?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.83,0:19:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,In our theme scripture,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.86,0:19:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul didn’t just say\Nto honor one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.53,0:19:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He said to “widen out” or reach out
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.64,0:19:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,in this aspect of our Christian life.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.61,0:19:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,His words were to “take the lead.”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.68,0:19:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,If Paul had just said\Nto show honor to each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.41,0:20:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that would be like a teacher
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.42,0:20:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,urging a group\Nof literate students to learn to read.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.15,0:20:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,If they’re literate,\Nthey don’t need to learn to read.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.39,0:20:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But what might the teacher\Nbe urging them to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.19,0:20:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He might encourage them\Nto read better, or to improve.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.93,0:20:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Love is the identifying mark\Nof Christ’s disciples.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.60,0:20:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So honor is something\Nwe’ve learned to show.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.74,0:20:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,However, like the teacher,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.41,0:20:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul is urging us\Nto improve in this area.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.11,0:20:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He said take the lead\Nin showing honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.02,0:20:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The footnote says\Nthis could be rendered
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.72,0:20:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,taking the “initiative”\Nin showing honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.19,0:20:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of waiting
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.39,0:20:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,for some obvious reason\Nto do good for others
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.50,0:20:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,—to commend someone,\Nto check on a shut-in—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.37,0:20:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,look for opportunities\Nto take the initiative
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.74,0:20:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to show honor in the family\Nand in our congregations.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.71,0:21:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, “in showing honor . . . ,\N take the lead”!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.48,0:21:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,At times, changing circumstances
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.88,0:21:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,can make it challenging to show honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.09,0:21:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,In this dramatization,\Nnote how the husband and wife
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.89,0:21:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,adjusted to a change while learning new ways
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.09,0:21:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to continue showing\Nlove and honor to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.87,0:21:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Kiara,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.24,0:21:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and that’s my husband, Shaan.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.85,0:21:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Our son Akil moved out recently
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.78,0:21:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to help where the need is greater.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.55,0:21:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t realize\Njust how much he made us laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.93,0:21:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I miss that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.90,0:21:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s just more quiet now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.70,0:22:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But more than that,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.47,0:22:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt we were growing apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.62,0:22:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried talking to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.73,0:22:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It didn’t go well.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.31,0:22:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since Akil left,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.55,0:22:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,things have been off\Nbetween Kiara and I.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.53,0:23:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,She is so serious now.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.90,0:23:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish she would just lighten up
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.17,0:23:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and laugh more,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.24,0:23:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,like when Akil was still here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.88,0:23:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,As much as I hated to admit it,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.88,0:23:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,it felt like we were growing apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.19,0:24:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Even Akil noticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.42,0:24:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, can I ask you guys a question?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.29,0:24:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you both doing OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.90,0:24:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you don’t look OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.93,0:24:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, we’re OK.\NOK?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.93,0:24:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re doing wonderful, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.00,0:24:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we’re doing good.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.03,0:24:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is good.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.87,0:24:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.74,0:24:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We weren’t fooling anyone
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.78,0:24:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,—except maybe ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.15,0:24:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And for the first time,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.42,0:24:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,we both revealed to each other
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.55,0:24:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,just how we had been really feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.59,0:24:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We knew we were headed down\Na dangerous path.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.79,0:24:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We had to do something\N—fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.30,0:24:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We read aloud the scripture
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.44,0:24:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,at Romans 12:10:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.87,0:24:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“In showing honor to one another,\Ntake the lead.”
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.45,0:25:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We thought about Abraham and Sarah.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.78,0:25:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,They weren’t perfect,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.42,0:25:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,but they worked hard\Nto show honor to each other
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.79,0:25:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,by listening and by caring.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.27,0:25:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I told Kiara, “I know I can do better.”
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.61,0:25:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And I wanted to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.88,0:25:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,because I love her so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.15,0:25:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I told Shaan,\N“Let’s both try to do better.”
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.82,0:25:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So we did.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.03,0:26:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,A few months later,\Nwe decided to pioneer together.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.87,0:26:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it seemed we had\Na lot to talk about.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.54,0:26:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt like I was seeing \Na whole new side of Kiara.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.28,0:26:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Like Abraham and Sarah,\Nour marriage wasn’t perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.52,0:26:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,There are going to be stressful times.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.86,0:26:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But by working hard\Nto apply Bible principles,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.43,0:26:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,we got through that rough patch
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.86,0:26:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and it drew us even closer together.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.33,0:27:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,First Corinthians 13:4, 7 tell us:
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.94,0:27:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“Love is patient and kind”\Nand “bears all things,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.68,0:27:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,believes all things,\Nhopes all things, endures all things.”
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.38,0:27:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Our dramatization helped us\Nto see how love can adapt
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.18,0:27:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to changing needs and circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.09,0:27:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But wouldn’t it be nice\Nto talk with some real-life examples
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.42,0:27:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of those who have developed such skills?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.46,0:27:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we have a special treat.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.86,0:27:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,A longtime faithful couple\Nhas joined us in the studio
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.44,0:27:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,—William and Angela Samuelson,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.87,0:27:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,who serve at Patterson Bethel\Nin the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.24,0:27:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, of course,\Nwe’ve known each other for decades,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.68,0:27:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and I know you as Bill and Angie,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.38,0:27:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,so that’s the way I’ll refer to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.75,0:27:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So nice that you\Ncould be here and be interviewed.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.35,0:27:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s helped you both\Nmaintain a happy marriage?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.89,0:27:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we work as a team,\Nso we always check
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.09,0:28:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,with each other\Nbefore making decisions,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.96,0:28:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,even in areas\Nwhere we wouldn’t necessarily have to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.30,0:28:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,—it would be OK to go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.30,0:28:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But just out of respect,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.64,0:28:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,we talk with each other\Nabout any decisions that we make.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.38,0:28:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know, Brother Morris,\Nwe’ve been married 60 years now,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.95,0:28:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’ve never really had\Na real serious argument.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.48,0:28:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve had some disagreements\Nbut nothing ever serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.62,0:28:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And whenever we have\Nthose kind of words, why, we never use
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.42,0:28:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,demeaning language or say\Nderogatory things about each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.10,0:28:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and that makes me very happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.70,0:28:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that’s commendable.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.33,0:28:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Early in our marriage,\Nthere was one occasion
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.04,0:28:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,when Angie was upset\Nwith me about something
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.07,0:28:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,—it could’ve been anything—
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.07,0:28:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and in the conversation,\Nit obviously showed in her tone of voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.48,0:28:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So I explained to her\Nthat she could say anything she wanted
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.35,0:28:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,as long as she smiled\Nwhen she said it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.45,0:29:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, she tried,\Nand we both had a good laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.09,0:29:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s very hard\Nto stay mad when you’re smiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.13,0:29:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Smiling—very, very good advice.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.69,0:29:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What about in the congregation?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.23,0:29:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,How have you been able\Nto show each other honor there?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.10,0:29:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, when we have assignments
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.14,0:29:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,from the platform,\Neither of us, we work together.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.97,0:29:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Angie is much better
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.18,0:29:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,with grammar\Nand pronunciation than I am,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.45,0:29:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and so I’ll check\Nwith her to make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.78,0:29:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that I’m saying things\Nas correctly as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.02,0:29:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And she checks with me
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.05,0:29:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,on prophetic significance, for example,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.92,0:29:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,or theocratic understanding\Nor procedure and timing.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.90,0:29:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, and something\Nthat’s very important
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.07,0:29:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is when we do check\Nwith each other, we’re not thin-skinned
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.07,0:29:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,about the advice\Nthat we want to give each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.84,0:29:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll call it advice.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.84,0:29:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And that makes life a lot easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.48,0:29:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We don’t get angry\Nbecause we’ve been told
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.78,0:30:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,we need to improve on something.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.12,0:30:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s excellent.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.28,0:30:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You also spent a long time
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.29,0:30:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,in the traveling work\Nbefore coming to Bethel.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.99,0:30:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We knew you in the traveling work\N—early ’70’s and then later
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.39,0:30:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,when we were down South\Nand you were assigned down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.90,0:30:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you learn\Nabout showing honor
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.03,0:30:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,in that avenue of service?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.97,0:30:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, as you say,\Nwe were in the traveling work
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.97,0:30:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,for 33 years, just over.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.51,0:30:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And for most of those years,\Nwe would have other assignments.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.41,0:30:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I would be working with the district
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.74,0:30:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,—now regional—\Nconvention organization
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.35,0:30:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,or other assignments,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.38,0:30:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and it meant\Nthat Angie would be alone
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.65,0:30:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,in the congregation.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.65,0:30:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,She never complained;
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.66,0:30:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,nor did she become unduly inquisitive\Nabout my assignment,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.09,0:30:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,which sometimes would’ve been confidential.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.50,0:30:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,When we had\Nan unexpected move that came up,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.40,0:30:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,a change of assignment somewhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.40,0:30:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Angie would just pack\Nand be ready to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.84,0:31:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s right.\NThat was my job—packing.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.81,0:31:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the field ministry, Brother Morris,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.28,0:31:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,we would usually be\Nin separate car groups
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.41,0:31:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,because Bill would work with the brothers\Nand I would work with the sisters.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.95,0:31:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And I really appreciated the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.15,0:31:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that he always made sure\NI had a safe driver.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.19,0:31:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It worked out most of the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.33,0:31:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we had a territory\Nthat was a little scary,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.16,0:31:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,why, he made sure\Nthat we were safe in the territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.40,0:31:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So I appreciated that very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.87,0:31:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,In one congregation,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.87,0:31:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,(you know, things\Ndon’t always go the way we plan)
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.68,0:31:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the brother scheduling the meals
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.31,0:31:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,had scheduled two families
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.31,0:31:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,for the same noon meal for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.45,0:31:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The one sister was deaf;
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.25,0:31:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and she had always had\Nthe traveling brother on a certain day;
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.82,0:31:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and she didn’t hear\Nwhen she was told it wouldn’t be that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.03,0:31:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So she had gone ahead\Nand prepared a meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.63,0:31:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,In the meantime,\Nwe had been assigned to another home,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.86,0:31:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,where they served us a full course
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.33,0:32:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,—or courses—\Nof an Italian meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.80,0:32:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,While we were eating, we found out
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.97,0:32:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that the other sister was waiting for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.07,0:32:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,She would’ve been highly offended\Nif somebody didn’t come.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.94,0:32:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So I went to the Kingdom Hall
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.05,0:32:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and handled the meeting\Nfor field service after the meal,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.95,0:32:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and Angie went to the sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.12,0:32:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That sister would probably\Nstill be mad at me if Angie hadn’t gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.15,0:32:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy, was I sleepy\Nthat afternoon after two big meals.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.83,0:32:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet.\NWell, you handled that very Christlike.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.70,0:32:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, as we mentioned,\Nyour current assignment is here at Bethel.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.00,0:32:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,How have you navigated\Nthe unique challenges
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.80,0:32:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of this form of service\Nwhile still honoring one another?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.67,0:32:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, as you know,\Nwe work in different departments,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.74,0:32:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,but we respect that some things
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.61,0:32:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,are confidential to that department.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.95,0:32:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So we don’t make\Nthe work of our department
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.05,0:32:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,a major part of our conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.06,0:32:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We could have an energy problem
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.89,0:32:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,at the end of the day after working all day,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.06,0:33:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so Bill is very considerate\Nabout accepting too many social invitations.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.00,0:33:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t that nice?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.13,0:33:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we respect\Neach other’s limitations
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.83,0:33:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,when it comes to physical
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.87,0:33:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and just energy in general.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.64,0:33:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that’s certainly honoring each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.08,0:33:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Bill and Angie,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.11,0:33:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,those were practical\Nand encouraging comments.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.98,0:33:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We really thank you so much
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.98,0:33:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,for taking the time\Nand allowing us to interview you,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.19,0:33:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and we really appreciate\Nyour good example all these decades.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.89,0:33:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.69,0:33:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.26,0:33:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,While the Samuelsons\Nare a wonderful example to try to imitate,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.27,0:33:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,we know that many marriages
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.50,0:33:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,may have a more difficult start,\Nor in some cases,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.97,0:33:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the mates may not share\Nthe same spiritual values.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.91,0:33:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What can be done if we find this\Nto be true in our case?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.25,0:33:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice how sister Grace Li
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.15,0:33:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,from Great Britain dealt\Nwith these challenges in her marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.89,0:34:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I was born in Hong Kong in 1952.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.36,0:34:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was just over 14 years of age,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.83,0:34:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,my mother sat me down and said,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.26,0:34:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“Look, there’s a marriage maker,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.47,0:34:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“and the gentleman has agreed
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.97,0:34:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to take you as his wife.”
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.24,0:34:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I was absolutely petrified!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.51,0:34:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I had never met him before.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.51,0:34:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,There was actually
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.51,0:34:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,a 20-year difference\Nbetween our ages,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.05,0:34:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,but I was willing to go through with it\Nbecause I love my mum.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.18,0:34:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted her to be able \Nto have a chance of happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.96,0:34:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I came to England, \Nand not long after that,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.23,0:34:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,we started our first \NChinese take-away in that little town.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.80,0:34:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to work very hard\Nseven days a week
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.13,0:34:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to help my husband \Nrun the business.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.67,0:34:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I was the only Chinese woman \Nin the entire town.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.38,0:34:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I had nowhere \Nto ask for help
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.41,0:35:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,or advice,\Nso I had a really bad time.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.55,0:35:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,When my second daughter was born,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.85,0:35:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,one night\Nshe just stopped breathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.56,0:35:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And a few minutes later, \Nthe nurse came out and said,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.66,0:35:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“God wanted a flower for his garden,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.43,0:35:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and that’s \Nwhere your daughter has gone.”
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.67,0:35:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So at that moment in time, \NI was very angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.40,0:35:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And I felt sad and sorrow and lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.51,0:35:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And I had horrible guilt:
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.07,0:35:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“It’s my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.51,0:35:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Or it’s God’s; it’s his fault.”
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.18,0:35:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So I stopped praying to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.38,0:35:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,One day, there was one very kind lady
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.69,0:35:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,who came and knocked on my door.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.19,0:35:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, eventually,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.26,0:35:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,one day, the ladies stopped\Nand had a conversation,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.16,0:35:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and the conversation led
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.27,0:35:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to why people die
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.53,0:35:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and what happens\Nwhen they’re dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.47,0:35:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Knowing it’s nobody’s fault
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.57,0:35:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,—it’s just our imperfection—
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.57,0:36:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I found it a great relief.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.58,0:36:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,God did not punish me for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.61,0:36:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And from then on,\NI started a Bible study with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.25,0:36:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But my study \Nwas progressing very slow.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.09,0:36:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,By that time, I had six children.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.29,0:36:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I also had to work full-time.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.76,0:36:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And also,\Nthe lady didn’t speak Chinese,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.80,0:36:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and my English was no better\Nthan her Chinese either.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.87,0:36:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Since I dedicated my life to Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.11,0:36:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s not been easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.17,0:36:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,As far as my husband was concerned,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.21,0:36:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,his wife should be concentrating
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.88,0:36:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,on looking after the family\Nand the business
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.88,0:36:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and shouldn’t be wasting time\Non religions like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.99,0:36:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,My mum, as well,\Nwas very much against me
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.15,0:36:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,becoming one of Jehovah’s Witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.29,0:36:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,My husband shouted at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.30,0:36:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Often he gave me a hard time\Nbecause I wanted to take
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.56,0:36:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,all my children to the meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.44,0:37:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,One day,\Nhe wanted me to choose
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.87,0:37:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,between him or Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.94,0:37:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And I prayed to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.21,0:37:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, “Jehovah, now is the time
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.01,0:37:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I need your holy spirit to help me.”
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.35,0:37:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said, \N“My husband is a good man,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.78,0:37:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“and he deserves to know why
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.82,0:37:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I chose this life.”
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.86,0:37:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And I just felt so calm,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.06,0:37:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and then I turned around\Nand asked my husband:
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.23,0:37:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“What do you think of me \Nsince I became a Witness?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.63,0:37:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I a better wife,\Nor am I getting worse?”
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.50,0:37:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So my husband said:\N“Oh, OK then.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.97,0:37:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,If that is the case,\Ngo serve your God, Jehovah.”
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.08,0:37:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Before my mother died,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.21,0:37:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,my mother actually prayed to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.92,0:37:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to thank him and to say
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.92,0:37:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that since I became\None of Jehovah’s Witnesses,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.52,0:37:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I became a better daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.53,0:38:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember, one day,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.49,0:38:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,one of my Bible students\Ncame to my house,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.53,0:38:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and she was crying
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.67,0:38:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,because she suffered\Npersecution from her husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.87,0:38:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And my husband\Nwas sitting next to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.44,0:38:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and he turned around and said,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.54,0:38:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“You just have to persevere,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.55,0:38:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“because my wife went through \Nthe same experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.42,0:38:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and look where she is now.”
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.25,0:38:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,For the last ten years,\Nmy husband has come
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.25,0:38:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to all the meetings with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.59,0:38:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Seeing my children happy\Nis the most important thing for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.66,0:38:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And they are happy\Nnot only for a short time
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.70,0:38:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,but they also have a happy future.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.87,0:38:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,My life now—I’m no longer lonely;
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.90,0:38:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m no longer a fatherless child,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.44,0:38:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,because I know Jehovah cares for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.08,0:38:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah helped a little woman like me,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.38,0:38:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and I’m sure Jehovah will help anybody
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.08,0:38:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,whose heart is toward him.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.28,0:38:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister Li’s example helps us to see
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.89,0:39:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that even in spiritually divided homes,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.69,0:39:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,applying Bible principles in our life
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.23,0:39:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,can often soften the heart\Nof our mate toward the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.76,0:39:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Having seen some beautiful examples
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.36,0:39:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of showing honor within our marriage,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.47,0:39:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s now look at ways of showing honor
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.74,0:39:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to one another in the congregation.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.57,0:39:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,For example,\Nwhat if we’re serving in a foreign territory
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.18,0:39:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,where the customs and culture
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.18,0:39:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,are quite different\Nfrom what we’re accustomed to?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.15,0:39:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just one of many challenges often faced
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.25,0:39:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,by ones involved\Nin the international construction work.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.09,0:39:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What have they found to be helpful
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.19,0:39:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,when adapting to new environments?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.45,0:41:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice the beautiful thought
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.25,0:41:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that every culture has its own strong points
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.62,0:41:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that we can learn from and apply in our lives?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.29,0:41:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What an excellent way to cultivate
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.39,0:41:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,an attitude of viewing others as superior!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.56,0:41:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But what about ones outside the congregation?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.00,0:42:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we show honor to them as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.50,0:42:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.50,0:42:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Galatians 6:10 tells us:
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.74,0:42:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“As long as we have the opportunity,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.21,0:42:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,let us work what is good toward all.”
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.21,0:42:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The best way we can do this is
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.28,0:42:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,by helping them cultivate\Nand satisfy their spiritual needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.62,0:42:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We now visit a town in the state\Nof Oregon in the United States
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.42,0:42:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,where the congregations\Nhad a unique opportunity to do just this.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.06,0:42:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,An exciting event took place
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.76,0:42:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,in 2017 across the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.70,0:42:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,August 21, 2017,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.34,0:42:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,has been on a lot of people’s calendars
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.07,0:42:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,for a long time because of the total eclipse.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.47,0:42:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,As Jehovah’s Witnesses,\Nwe are constantly on the lookout
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.91,0:42:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,for events where we can support\Ncommunity outreach.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.15,0:42:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.28,0:42:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,prepared well in advance\Nto give a Bible education
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.32,0:42:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to the many travelers.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.95,0:42:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What convinced us\Nthat this was an opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.59,0:42:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to give a great witness\Nwas that we did a little research,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.06,0:43:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and we noticed the hotel bookings.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.16,0:43:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The town was packed,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.06,0:43:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,so we could tell\Nthat this was going to be a big event.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.13,0:43:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We needed to do something.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.40,0:43:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We wanted to be in a position to share
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.67,0:43:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the wonderful things from the Bible with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.41,0:43:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We needed to take a global approach.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.04,0:43:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We had to identify\Nall the resources in Bend
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.48,0:43:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and not just do it\Nby individual congregation.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.18,0:43:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So in our campaign we decided\Nto feature three primary tools:
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.38,0:43:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,first, What Does the Bible Really Teach?\Nbecause many people wonder;
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.19,0:43:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,second, Was Life Created?\Nbecause with an eclipse event,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.29,0:43:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,people are thinking about the universe,\Nand it’s a good opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.16,0:43:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to talk about our Creator;
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.63,0:43:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and third,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.30,0:43:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,jw.org,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.13,0:43:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,since we expect a lot of visitors\Nfrom all over the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.94,0:43:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,we can reach them in their language.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.77,0:43:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 200 brothers and sisters\Nattended two seminars
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.98,0:43:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,put on by local brothers to help prepare\Nindividuals for the massive campaign.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.21,0:43:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We had examples\Nof what not to do and what to do
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.65,0:44:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,so as to benefit\Nas many people as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.66,0:44:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We had an interview;
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.96,0:44:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,we had demonstrations on how to speak\Nto people in different languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.30,0:44:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re expecting people\Nfrom many different parts of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.07,0:44:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s actually an opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.30,0:44:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to be like a missionary\Nin our own hometown.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.97,0:44:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of the estimates\Nthat we have heard are conservative estimates
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.81,0:44:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of probably 200,000 visitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.88,0:44:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It may be more than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.45,0:44:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The local congregations\Nmade themselves available
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.28,0:44:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to work with city officials
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.35,0:44:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to prepare the parks\Nfor the large influx of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.56,0:44:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So many of Jehovah’s Witnesses\Nhave volunteered
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.49,0:44:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to help with all kinds of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.99,0:44:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,These are really small communities\Nthat are having a very large influx of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.77,0:44:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So all of that extra effort
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.77,0:44:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and help in kind of preparing and cleaning up
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.54,0:44:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is much appreciated.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.24,0:44:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We have been working with Jehovah’s Witnesses
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.31,0:44:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,for a period of years here at Smith Rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.84,0:44:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s been a good experience\Nfor our staff and our volunteers,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.75,0:45:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and we want to accommodate that\Nin any way we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.22,0:45:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s been a lot of good things\Nhappening with cart witnessing.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.35,0:45:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the friends had a nice experience\Nwith an Arabic-speaking man,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.66,0:45:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and she said the seminar \Nis what helped her to be prepared.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.29,0:45:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,She knew how to work the app,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.30,0:45:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,how to find the video in the language,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.33,0:45:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and she already\Nhad it downloaded and ready to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.30,0:45:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul spoke about his ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.34,0:45:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He said: “Woe is me\Nif I did not declare the good news!”
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.41,0:45:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So we don’t want to look back\Nand wish we would’ve done more.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.65,0:45:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Trying it for the first time can be scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.08,0:45:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be nerve-racking,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.21,0:45:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,but it’s not so scary after you get started.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.79,0:45:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s really been fun\Nis what we are calling roving.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.49,0:45:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We go into an area\Nwhere there are a lot of people,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.63,0:45:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and we just start conversations.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.76,0:45:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We don’t carry any literature.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.80,0:45:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We just have our device
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.50,0:45:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and the jw.org contact card.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.33,0:45:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, hopefully,\Nif the opportunity presents itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.87,0:45:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,we may share with them a video
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.34,0:46:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,or tell them\Nwe’re Jehovah’s Witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.64,0:46:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s just been a paradise for them
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.51,0:46:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,—a preaching paradise—\Nall these visitors coming in.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.61,0:46:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We may not see the results
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.15,0:46:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,of the seed that was planted\Nwhen they took a look at our cart,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.98,0:46:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,but Jehovah knows
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.19,0:46:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and the angels know\Nand can make that grow.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.29,0:46:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,This endeavor\Nhas really helped me to appreciate
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.89,0:46:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,the need to be alert\Nto ways to expand our ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.00,0:46:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Most communities have a calendar of events.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.47,0:46:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Have we thought about looking at it
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.70,0:46:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and then making plans to give a witness
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.94,0:46:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,by having our literature carts out?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.21,0:46:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And, really, events like this,\Nthey have a bigger impact
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.48,0:46:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,on us as Jehovah’s Witnesses\Nbecause we have an opportunity to talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.18,0:46:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We get excited about our work.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.28,0:46:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re all working together shoulder to shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.55,0:46:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It really builds our faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.56,0:46:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Recently, a scripture\Nthat stood out to me was 1 Chronicles 28:20,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.56,0:46:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,where it says:\N“Be courageous . . . and go to work.”
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.23,0:47:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It helped me to realize\Nthat I just need to take the initiative and try.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.77,0:47:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what we all need to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.00,0:47:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and then let Jehovah\Ndecide how things turn out.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.47,0:47:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will no doubt bless your efforts
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.21,0:47:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,as you show an interest in others.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.75,0:47:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The interest we show\Nin others is most noteworthy
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.09,0:47:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,within the bounds of our own brotherhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.52,0:47:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Galatians 6:10, which we quoted earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.59,0:47:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,ends its thought\Nabout working “good toward all,”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.96,0:47:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,saying that we should do this
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.96,0:47:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“especially toward those\Nrelated to us in the faith.”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.73,0:47:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Our music video entitled\NYou Can Count on Me
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.70,0:47:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,provides a touching example\Nof how this “good” can be shown.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.25,0:47:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Time and circumstance\NDon’t always work in our favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.96,0:48:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What might have been\Nif we just had the chance
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.17,0:48:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Is something\Nwe may never know.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.07,0:48:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But God looks down and sees;\NHe knows us better than we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.88,0:48:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,He sees what we are\Nand what more we could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.62,0:48:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s all in the way\Nthat we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.23,0:48:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,He values all of us,\NNo matter what talent or gift we possess.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.51,0:48:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants each one of us\NTo be as caring as he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.35,0:49:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So you’re my friend\N’cause you’re always there
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.52,0:49:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Through our ups and downs\Nand through all we’ve shared.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.43,0:49:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And I’m there \NWhen you need someone,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.60,0:49:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,when things\Nare hard to bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.10,0:49:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll be the friend you need.\NYou can count on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.72,0:49:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We weep with those who weep,\NSharing the things that we’re feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.76,0:49:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But sometimes our tears\Nmay be all that can speak,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.80,0:49:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Expressing what words cannot say.\NTroubles can bring us down.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.24,0:50:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah can lift us\Nand carry us through.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.12,0:50:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We all can do the same\NAnd help each other as friends do.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.66,0:50:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And you’re my friend\N’cause you’re always there
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.77,0:50:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Through our ups and downs\Nand through all we’ve shared.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.90,0:50:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And I’m there\NWhen you need someone,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.01,0:50:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,when things\Nare hard to bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.98,0:50:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll be the friend you need.\NYou can count on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.21,0:51:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And you’re my friend\N’cause you’re always there
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.08,0:51:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Through our ups and downs\Nand through all we’ve shared.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.85,0:51:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And I’m there\NWhen you need someone,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.02,0:51:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,when things\Nare hard to bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.02,0:51:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll be the friend you need.\NYou can count on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.41,0:51:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We conclude this month’s program\Nby traveling to Indonesia.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.68,0:51:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Composed of more than 17,000 islands,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.81,0:51:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,it consists of hundreds of distinct native,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.78,0:51:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,ethnic, and linguistic groups,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.15,0:51:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,with the largest being the Javanese.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.72,0:51:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s visit the city of Malang,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.72,0:51:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,which has some 370 publishers
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.63,0:51:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,in 9 congregations.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.63,0:51:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The territory here is productive,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.80,0:52:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,with many who are open to the Bible’s message.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.13,0:52:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The largest challenge\Nour brothers face here is economic hardship.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.77,0:52:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not easy to provide even basic necessities,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.14,0:52:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,so many people in the territory work long hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.08,0:52:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the pioneers
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.11,0:52:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,have found an ingenious way to make a living
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.78,0:52:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,making milk, juice, and cakes from soybeans.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.92,0:52:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,A typical day will have them up at 3:00 a.m.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.19,0:52:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,making fresh soy products
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.19,0:52:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and then selling them\Non the street in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.03,0:52:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,In the afternoon they preach\Nand go to the market that evening
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.23,0:52:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to buy fresh ingredients\Nfor the next day’s work.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.60,0:52:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,While the brothers in Malang\Nhave not yet been able to obtain a permit
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.77,0:52:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,for an official Kingdom Hall,\Nthey often meet in private homes.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.74,0:52:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Although it can be cramped and hot,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.85,0:52:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,attendance is\Nnearly always well over 100 percent.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.62,0:52:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The publishers in Malang
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.59,0:52:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,send their warm love and greetings
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.02,0:52:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to our entire global brotherhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.49,0:52:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,This is JW Broadcasting
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.49,0:53:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,from the world headquarters\Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses.
